ce:section.ce:para:
The purpose of this work is to prepare a class of water-soluble CQDs from polyacrylamide(PAM)through one-step hydrothermal method (Fig. 1
                     ), which exhibits excellent stability in acidic and alkaline media. In addition, as a carbon source, PAM is a water-soluble polymer, as well itself and its hydrolysates are nontoxic [59,60]. Furthermore, to confirm the practicality of this fluorescence probe, it is further applied to measure the Hg(II) in tap water and waste water samples. The fluorescent carbon quantum dots shows high sensitivity and selectivity for the detection of Hg2+ based on the efficient fluorescence quenching. It displays a linear quenching effect toward mercury ion in the concentration range of 0.25–50μM with a favorable linear correlation (R2
                     =0.9988). The limit of detection is determined to be 13.48nM at the signal to noise ratio of 3.The prepared CQDs probe for selective and sensitive detection of Hg(II).
